| Trivia                  = * In the comics, [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]] usually operates out of [[New York (State)|New York]] on the East Coast, but director [[Jon Favreau]] wanted to relocate him to the West Coast for the film to differentiate it from other superhero films like ''[[Spider-Man (2002 film)|Spider-Man]]'' and ''[[Fantastic Four (2005 film)|Fantastic Four]]''.{{cite|ref=true|url=http://www.aintitcool.com/node/31525|title=Quint visits the IRON MAN production offices! Art! Favreau speaks about sequels (?!?), casting and more!!!|author=Quint|work=Ain't It Cool News|date=9 February 2007|accessdate=3 March 2018}}
* Director and co-star Jon Favreau had previously appeared as the Marvel character [[Franklin Nelson (Earth-701306)|Franklin "Foggy" Nelson]] in the 2003 film ''[[Daredevil (film)|Daredevil]]''.
* When shown on FX, the water torture scene was removed and replaced with a scene that was originally deleted.{{citation}}
* An earlier version of the scene in which Tony replaces his arc reactor at his lab didn't feature Pepper. Instead, Tony operated a machine on his own to replace the reactor.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BjDNxThAcLq/|title=Ryan Meinerding on Instagram: "Another look back at the first Iron Man. This was an idea that @jonfavreau had for when Tony is working on his RT. Instead this moment in…"|work=Instagram|first=Ryan|last=Meinerding|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=22 May 2018}}
* The basic concept of showing Tony's face from inside his armor helmet with the suit's HUD displayed in front of him was inspired by the film ''[[wikipedia:2001: Space Odyssey|2001: Space Odyssey]]'', namely the shots in which the lights on a computer are reflected in the helmet of the astronaut David Bowman.{{cite|ref=true|refname=HUD|url=https://news.avclub.com/nerd-out-like-tony-stark-with-this-breakdown-of-how-the-1825732473|title=Nerd out like Tony Stark with this breakdown of how the Iron Man HUD was created|work=AV News|first=Sam|last=Barsanti|date=2 May 2018|accessdate=13 August 2018}}
* An early cut of the film included a sequence that explained how the Iron Man helmet worked and the purpose of the HUD. The sequence was scrapped after test audiences managed to grasp the concept of the HUD immediately and were actually more confused by the attempts to explain it.<ref name="HUD"/>
* Tony Stark's reveal that he was Iron Man at the end of the movie was originally ad-libbed by Robert Downey Jr.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/iron-man-10th-anniversary-marvel-robert-downey-jr-kevin-feige-jon-favreau-comic-con-1202428754/|title=‘Iron Man’ At 10: How One Film Set A Dominant Path For Marvel, Kevin Feige, Robert Downey Jr. & Jon Favreau|work=Deadline|first=Geoff|last=Boucher|date=19 July 2018|accessdate=24 July 2018}}
